Former Goldman Employee Accused of Insider Trading in ETF by SEC

-- B y   V i v e k   S h a n k a r
-- 
2011-09-21T17:51:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/former-goldman-employee-accused-of-insider-trading-in-etf-by-sec.html
A former  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. (GS) 
employee and his father were accused of insider trading by the
U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  Spencer D. Mindlin obtained non-public details about
Goldman’s plans to purchase and sell large amounts of securities
underlying the  SPDR S&P Retail ETF (XRT)  and tipped off his father
Alfred C. Mindlin, a certified public accountant, the SEC said
in a  statement .  The two then illegaly traded in four different securities,
the SEC claimed. The case marks the agency’s first insider
trading enforcement action involving ETFs, according to the
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vivek Shankar at 
 vshankar3@bloomberg.net  